      "note_no": "1889",
      "note": "Cf. 8:19. 1 have assumed that \"they\" in this verse is the same as \"them\" in the preceding verse, i.e., the ungodly. Hoping for victory, they forced a decision, and they got it-against themselves. Or they challenged a punishment, and it came in good time. Some Commentators construe \"they\" here to mean \"the Prophets\"; in that case the verse would mean: \"The Prophets prayed for a victory and decision, and the ungodly were frustrated in their efforts to suppress the Truth.\""
